<li id="cite_note-47"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-47">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">For instance <a href="#CITEREFWald1984">Wald 1984</a>, sec. 4.4</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-48"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFWill1993">Will 1993</a>, sec. 4.1 and 4.2</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFWill2006">Will 2006</a>, sec. 3.2, <a href="#CITEREFWill1993">Will 1993</a>, ch. 4</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFRindler2001">Rindler 2001</a>, pp.&#160;24–26 vs. pp. 236–237 and <a href="#CITEREFOhanianRuffini1994">Ohanian &amp; Ruffini 1994</a>, pp.&#160;164–172. Einstein derived these effects using the equivalence principle as early as 1907, cf. <a href="#CITEREFEinstein1907">Einstein 1907</a> and the description in <a href="#CITEREFPais1982">Pais 1982</a>, pp.&#160;196–198</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFRindler2001">Rindler 2001</a>, pp.&#160;24–26; <a href="#CITEREFMisnerThorneWheeler1973">Misner, Thorne &amp; Wheeler 1973</a>, § 38.5</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Pound-Rebka_experiment" title="Pound-Rebka experiment" class="mw-redirect">Pound-Rebka experiment</a>, see <a href="#CITEREFPoundRebka1959">Pound &amp; Rebka 1959</a>, <a href="#CITEREFPoundRebka1960">Pound &amp; Rebka 1960</a>; <a href="#CITEREFPoundSnider1964">Pound &amp; Snider 1964</a>; a list of further experiments is given in <a href="#CITEREFOhanianRuffini1994">Ohanian &amp; Ruffini 1994</a>, table 4.1 on p. 186</span></li>
